1
00:00:01,120 --> 00:00:07,340
I'm sure the girl Kusaka-kun
ends up dating will be happy.

2
00:00:08,150 --> 00:00:11,040
- Looks like you had fun yesterday.
- Huh?

3
00:00:11,040 --> 00:00:15,115
Let's go together again
if I find another delicious restaurant.

4
00:00:15,115 --> 00:00:17,015
Yeah.

5
00:00:17,015 --> 00:00:18,820
So direct, huh?

6
00:00:18,820 --> 00:00:20,930
Not at all.

7
00:00:20,930 --> 00:00:22,930
But whatever.

8
00:00:26,520 --> 00:00:28,020
Hey.

9
00:00:30,096 --> 00:00:32,526
What did you two chat about?

10
00:00:37,140 --> 00:00:39,380
What did you do with him?

11
00:00:44,640 --> 00:00:46,670
I won't tell you.

12
00:00:54,888 --> 00:00:59,830
If we were dating, would it be like this?

13
00:00:59,830 --> 00:01:02,620
Are you gushing or conflicted? Which is it?

14
00:01:02,620 --> 00:01:04,498
I'm conflicted.

15
00:01:04,498 --> 00:01:07,823
It's up to you, Mihono.
I've told you this.

16
00:01:08,920 --> 00:01:12,030
Yeah, you're right.

17
00:01:15,110 --> 00:01:17,720
What is this?

18
00:01:17,720 --> 00:01:19,780
- Ureshino-san.
- Here.

19
00:01:19,780 --> 00:01:21,710
- Kusaka-san.
- Here.

20
00:01:21,710 --> 00:01:23,870
- Onuma-san.
- Here.

21
00:01:23,870 --> 00:01:26,175
- Everyone's here.
- Thank you.

22
00:01:27,385 --> 00:01:29,000
We'll be departing shortly.

23
00:01:29,000 --> 00:01:31,430
Enjoy the journey to Rinkai Hot Springs!

24
00:01:31,430 --> 00:01:35,240
Yeah!

25
00:01:36,340 --> 00:01:39,980
How did things turn out like this?

26
00:01:42,495 --> 00:01:44,373
Ureshino-san.

27
00:01:44,373 --> 00:01:46,580
Isn't it tight with three people?

28
00:01:46,580 --> 00:01:49,260
If you'd like, there's space next to me.

29
00:01:49,260 --> 00:01:51,435
No, I'm actually fine here.

30
00:01:51,435 --> 00:01:53,625
Really?

31
00:01:54,848 --> 00:01:58,110
Did you hear that, Ureshino-kun?
Yuri-chan is so kind.

32
00:01:58,110 --> 00:01:59,745
Why don't you go to the front?

33
00:01:59,745 --> 00:02:01,165
Go on.

34
00:02:02,110 --> 00:02:03,880
Over here.

35
00:02:17,820 --> 00:02:21,640
♫ It's hard to resist the thing
that I've missed for so long ♫

36
00:02:21,640 --> 00:02:23,500
♫ So long ♫

37
00:02:23,500 --> 00:02:27,250
♫ Can't remember what it's like,
Just remember I need it ♫

38
00:02:27,250 --> 00:02:29,730
♫ I need it ♫

39
00:02:29,730 --> 00:02:33,940
♫ You're not what I thought you were ♫

40
00:02:33,940 --> 00:02:35,850
♫ You were ♫

41
00:02:35,850 --> 00:02:39,320
♫ To think I can't find a cure ♫

42
00:02:39,320 --> 00:02:41,890
♫ Find a cure ♫

43
00:02:41,890 --> 00:02:47,940
♫ Ooh, you're not what I thought ♫

44
00:02:51,030 --> 00:02:58,400
[If Only You Weren't the One]

45
00:02:58,400 --> 00:03:02,465
[Episode 4]

46
00:03:02,465 --> 00:03:05,530
Yes, we have an annual trip
to the hot springs.

47
00:03:05,530 --> 00:03:08,070
It's optional, but it's part of our benefits,

48
00:03:08,070 --> 00:03:09,990
so almost everyone goes.

49
00:03:09,990 --> 00:03:11,950
Oh, that's nice.

50
00:03:11,950 --> 00:03:14,500
- Is it an overnight stay?
- Of course!

51
00:03:14,500 --> 00:03:18,410
- They even launch fireworks at night.
- Wow, amazing.

52
00:03:18,410 --> 00:03:21,000
- Have a good time.
- Huh?

53
00:03:21,000 --> 00:03:24,540
Oh, I just got hired recently,
so I don't know anyone.

54
00:03:24,540 --> 00:03:28,590
- Please go without me.
- No, no, please join us, Ureshino-san.

55
00:03:28,590 --> 00:03:30,965
Thank you.

56
00:03:31,770 --> 00:03:34,210
But still...

57
00:03:35,535 --> 00:03:38,090
Don't other departments go?

58
00:03:38,090 --> 00:03:41,090
Oh, it's totally fine if they want to come.

59
00:03:41,090 --> 00:03:43,390
I wouldn't call it
a company-wide trip, though.

60
00:03:43,390 --> 00:03:47,005
- Why do you ask?
- Well...

61
00:03:47,005 --> 00:03:51,490
- I was thinking I'd like to go if Onuma-san is going, too.
- Huh?

62
00:03:51,490 --> 00:03:56,605
We're somewhat acquainted,
so I'd feel more comfortable.

63
00:03:56,605 --> 00:03:59,440
If not, maybe I'll pass this time.

64
00:04:02,170 --> 00:04:04,060
Got it.

65
00:04:04,060 --> 00:04:06,920
Yeah, you're right.

66
00:04:08,335 --> 00:04:11,140
Oh, Mihono-san, there you are!

67
00:04:11,140 --> 00:04:13,240
Yuri-chan, what is it?

68
00:04:13,240 --> 00:04:17,595
Mihono-san, I have a huge favor to ask!

69
00:04:17,595 --> 00:04:19,080
Huh?

70
00:04:25,635 --> 00:04:28,570
I'm glad you're joining us, too.

71
00:04:28,570 --> 00:04:30,100
Really?

72
00:04:30,100 --> 00:04:32,430
But aren't I out of place?

73
00:04:32,430 --> 00:04:34,150
Not at all.

74
00:04:34,150 --> 00:04:37,005
Since you're here, let's enjoy ourselves.

75
00:04:37,005 --> 00:04:39,975
Yeah, you're right. Thanks.

76
00:04:43,110 --> 00:04:45,030
Ureshino-san.

77
00:04:45,030 --> 00:04:47,920
- Thank you for coming.
- Of course.

78
00:04:47,920 --> 00:04:50,755
If you need anything,
you can always ask me.

79
00:04:50,755 --> 00:04:54,035
Yoshiki-san, thank you.

80
00:04:55,705 --> 00:04:59,285
- Also, you don't need to use formal language with me.
- Huh?

81
00:04:59,285 --> 00:05:04,816
Well, you're older than me,
and you know a lot about work stuff too.

82
00:05:04,816 --> 00:05:06,600
- You think so?
- Yes.

83
00:05:06,600 --> 00:05:09,430
Honestly, I'd prefer it that way.

84
00:05:09,430 --> 00:05:13,280
Well, it's hard to be casual
from the get-go, but I'll try.

85
00:05:13,280 --> 00:05:15,760
Okay. Please do.

86
00:05:15,760 --> 00:05:19,750
- I love your outfit.
- Huh? Really?

87
00:05:19,750 --> 00:05:22,022
- Yeah, it suits you.
- I'm so glad.

88
00:05:22,022 --> 00:05:23,908
Ureshino-san, do you like dresses?

89
00:05:23,908 --> 00:05:26,093
Dresses? If they suit the person.

90
00:05:26,093 --> 00:05:28,878
- Really?
- It suits you.

91
00:05:28,878 --> 00:05:31,210
We'll stop here for 30 minutes.

92
00:05:31,210 --> 00:05:32,710
Okay.

93
00:05:32,710 --> 00:05:34,235
Phew.

94
00:05:34,235 --> 00:05:37,375
Wow, this feels great.

95
00:05:44,770 --> 00:05:47,620
This is so tiring.

96
00:05:47,620 --> 00:05:50,040
I have to be mindful as a guest.

97
00:05:50,040 --> 00:05:53,415
Why am I even here in the first place?

98
00:05:53,415 --> 00:05:55,385
Miporin.

99
00:05:56,100 --> 00:05:58,010
Want a bite?

100
00:05:59,070 --> 00:06:02,110
This crepe place is popular. Look.

101
00:06:05,640 --> 00:06:07,600
I'll pass.

102
00:06:08,415 --> 00:06:12,200
Oh, so you really
do prefer Kusaka-kun after all.

103
00:06:12,200 --> 00:06:13,340
Excuse me?

104
00:06:13,340 --> 00:06:17,365
You forced me to sit up front
and had a good time together.

105
00:06:17,365 --> 00:06:19,685
You're so tacky.

106
00:06:20,630 --> 00:06:22,700
How so?

107
00:06:22,700 --> 00:06:27,230
You're a nuisance.
You just want to tease me, right?

108
00:06:34,740 --> 00:06:36,580
That's not it.

109
00:06:37,360 --> 00:06:40,860
I just wanted to do
something like this with you.

110
00:06:43,860 --> 00:06:49,270
Because whenever we meet,
it's always at our apartments or a hotel.

111
00:06:50,410 --> 00:06:52,330
Oh, no.

112
00:06:52,330 --> 00:06:54,140
This is bad.

113
00:06:56,010 --> 00:06:59,210
He's not in a suit today...

114
00:07:21,450 --> 00:07:26,590
I'm being pulled back to ten years ago.

115
00:07:30,370 --> 00:07:32,270
Onuma-san.

116
00:07:35,685 --> 00:07:38,340
Aren't you a little hungry?

117
00:07:38,340 --> 00:07:41,930
There's a delicious-looking skewer shop.

118
00:07:41,930 --> 00:07:44,900
Yeah, sounds good. Let's go.

119
00:07:45,980 --> 00:07:49,080
Want to come, Ureshino-san?

120
00:07:49,080 --> 00:07:51,510
Oh...

121
00:07:52,350 --> 00:07:55,070
I'm fine.

122
00:07:55,070 --> 00:07:58,620
Then let's go, Onuma-san.

123
00:07:58,620 --> 00:08:00,120
Okay.

124
00:08:16,575 --> 00:08:18,410
- Thank you very much.
- Thank you very much.

125
00:08:18,410 --> 00:08:20,680
- Let's go over there.
- Okay.

126
00:08:22,900 --> 00:08:24,880
It's so hot.

127
00:08:24,880 --> 00:08:27,240
- Are you okay?
- Yeah!

128
00:08:27,240 --> 00:08:31,735
- But it's so delicious.
- It really is.

129
00:08:39,515 --> 00:08:42,360
Ureshino-san, I finally found you.

130
00:08:42,360 --> 00:08:45,320
Oh, that crepe looks so good.

131
00:08:45,320 --> 00:08:46,995
- Want a bite?
- Really?

132
00:08:46,995 --> 00:08:49,405
Sure. Open wide.

133
00:08:51,350 --> 00:08:54,100
- Is it good?
- It's so good.

134
00:08:54,100 --> 00:08:57,910
Onuma-san, should we go look at
other things after eating this?

135
00:08:57,910 --> 00:08:59,685
Yeah.

136
00:08:59,685 --> 00:09:02,250
Here. Open wide.

137
00:09:03,190 --> 00:09:05,815
- Is it good?
- It's so good!

138
00:09:06,620 --> 00:09:11,270
To be honest, I wanted something sweet.

139
00:09:12,120 --> 00:09:16,480
I had wanted to eat those strawberries.

140
00:09:28,650 --> 00:09:32,535
[Rinkai Manor]

141
00:09:32,535 --> 00:09:35,280
Yuri-chan, that looks so warm. It suits you.

142
00:09:35,280 --> 00:09:37,380
Thank you. It's my favorite.

143
00:09:37,380 --> 00:09:39,370
Oh, nice.

144
00:09:39,370 --> 00:09:42,300
I'm so glad I get to room with you.

145
00:09:42,300 --> 00:09:44,230
- Let's have fun tonight, too.
- Yeah.

146
00:09:44,230 --> 00:09:47,020
I'm glad I'm with you, too.

147
00:09:47,020 --> 00:09:50,680
Actually, I've gotten super close
to Ureshino-san on this trip.

148
00:09:50,680 --> 00:09:53,540
- I'll tell you more later.
- Sure, tell me.

149
00:09:53,540 --> 00:09:56,410
We're watching the fireworks together.

150
00:09:56,410 --> 00:09:58,670
Nice work! You never miss a beat.

151
00:09:58,670 --> 00:10:00,499
- What's that?
- It's a heart.

152
00:10:00,499 --> 00:10:02,928
A heart? So cute.

153
00:10:02,928 --> 00:10:05,555
Oh, Ureshino-san!

154
00:10:06,315 --> 00:10:07,250
You look so cool!

155
00:10:07,250 --> 00:10:09,590
Really? Thanks.

156
00:10:09,590 --> 00:10:11,560
- Where's the coat from?
- The coat?

157
00:10:11,560 --> 00:10:13,790
I wonder where I got it. It's a secret.

158
00:10:13,790 --> 00:10:15,775
A secret? Come on...

159
00:10:15,775 --> 00:10:17,435
Onuma-san.

160
00:10:19,190 --> 00:10:22,320
Would you like to go together?

161
00:10:23,350 --> 00:10:25,350
Yeah.

162
00:10:25,350 --> 00:10:27,920
The hat suits you.

163
00:10:28,675 --> 00:10:30,801
My only defense against the cold.

164
00:10:30,801 --> 00:10:32,310
It's cute.

165
00:10:32,310 --> 00:10:34,250
Thanks.

166
00:10:34,250 --> 00:10:39,460
By the way, after the fireworks today,
we're all going to drink together.

167
00:10:39,460 --> 00:10:41,020
Will you join us?

168
00:10:41,020 --> 00:10:43,240
Well, I'm not sure...

169
00:10:43,240 --> 00:10:45,112
Come join us. Let's make the most of it.

170
00:10:45,112 --> 00:10:48,737
Hmm... I'll think about it.

171
00:10:49,995 --> 00:10:51,320
White suits you.

172
00:10:51,320 --> 00:10:52,620
Really?

173
00:10:52,620 --> 00:10:54,570
You look kind of sharp and cool, too.

174
00:10:54,570 --> 00:10:56,785
Should we go too?

175
00:10:56,785 --> 00:10:58,615
- Okay.
- Yes.

176
00:10:59,285 --> 00:11:02,140
- I can't wait.
- Me too.

177
00:11:03,865 --> 00:11:06,680
- I wonder how far it is.
- Yeah.

178
00:11:09,197 --> 00:11:12,310
I'm glad the skies cleared up, though.

179
00:11:12,310 --> 00:11:14,590
I can't wait.

180
00:11:15,325 --> 00:11:17,370
I haven't seen fireworks in a while.

181
00:11:17,370 --> 00:11:19,550
Yeah, me neither.

182
00:11:21,715 --> 00:11:23,700
- Oh, it's a whale!
- Huh? A whale?

183
00:11:23,700 --> 00:11:24,915
- Over there.
- Where?

184
00:11:24,915 --> 00:11:28,470
- I was kidding.
- You were? Stop teasing me.

185
00:11:28,470 --> 00:11:31,550
I'll take a picture. Say cheese!

186
00:11:31,550 --> 00:11:33,790
- Looking good.
- Can I see?

187
00:11:33,790 --> 00:11:37,550
- I'll take your photo too.
- I'm so excited.

188
00:11:37,550 --> 00:11:39,410
Free time!

189
00:11:46,530 --> 00:11:49,040
- Ouch...
- Are you okay?

190
00:11:50,560 --> 00:11:52,400
Jeez...

191
00:11:52,400 --> 00:11:55,570
I feel so dumb.

192
00:11:55,570 --> 00:11:57,570
Onuma-san!

193
00:12:00,055 --> 00:12:04,470
I wore my boots here,
so it's kind of hard to walk.

194
00:12:04,470 --> 00:12:08,420
Coming to a place like this,
doing things I'm not used to...

195
00:12:08,420 --> 00:12:11,710
Maybe I should just go back and rest.

196
00:12:11,710 --> 00:12:14,455
I'm really getting tired of this.

197
00:12:14,455 --> 00:12:16,125
It's okay.

198
00:12:19,650 --> 00:12:22,240
Let's go slowly.

199
00:12:38,895 --> 00:12:41,390
Sorry for causing you trouble.

200
00:12:41,390 --> 00:12:43,711
It's no trouble at all.

201
00:12:43,711 --> 00:12:47,051
From my perspective, I'm lucky.

202
00:12:51,425 --> 00:12:56,870
Did you and Ureshino-san use to date?

203
00:12:56,870 --> 00:12:58,270
Huh?

204
00:12:59,585 --> 00:13:01,280
Why?

205
00:13:01,280 --> 00:13:05,335
Well, I got the feeling
that you weren't just friends.

206
00:13:05,335 --> 00:13:07,195
No way.

207
00:13:09,435 --> 00:13:11,780
When we were in college,

208
00:13:11,780 --> 00:13:19,325
Ureshino-kun had a cute girlfriend,
and I had a long-term boyfriend too.

209
00:13:41,015 --> 00:13:42,510
In other words,

210
00:13:42,510 --> 00:13:46,470
it's a relationship
you can't describe through words.

211
00:13:48,625 --> 00:13:54,760
But if I said that,
Kusaka-kun would probably loathe me.

212
00:13:54,760 --> 00:13:57,990
So, we really are just friends.

213
00:13:58,790 --> 00:14:01,690
Oh, what a relief.

214
00:14:02,350 --> 00:14:06,140
Then, I won't hesitate
to invite you out from now on.

215
00:14:09,280 --> 00:14:13,890
If only I could be true to these feelings,

216
00:14:13,890 --> 00:14:16,540
things would be so much easier.

217
00:14:39,780 --> 00:14:42,380
- Is it around here?
- Yeah.

218
00:14:48,265 --> 00:14:52,150
Mihono-san! Kusaka-san! Over here!

219
00:15:01,330 --> 00:15:03,570
I won't hold back.

220
00:15:07,160 --> 00:15:10,975
Whoa. Those two
are suddenly getting close, huh?

221
00:15:23,056 --> 00:15:26,180
- I'm excited about the fireworks.
- Mm.

222
00:15:26,180 --> 00:15:28,355
Onuma-san, do you feel cold?

223
00:15:28,355 --> 00:15:31,655
No, I'm fine. Thanks.

224
00:15:40,280 --> 00:15:45,070
My heart is filled by his gentle hand.

225
00:15:46,000 --> 00:15:47,500
Ah.

226
00:16:25,660 --> 00:16:28,080
You're finally looking at me.

227
00:16:32,450 --> 00:16:34,910
They're so pretty.

228
00:16:34,910 --> 00:16:37,227
They sure are.

229
00:16:46,645 --> 00:16:51,210
My desires are about to explode.

230
00:16:59,825 --> 00:17:03,270
What is it that has such a hold over me?

231
00:17:03,270 --> 00:17:05,420
The thrill?

232
00:17:06,180 --> 00:17:08,400
The possessiveness?

233
00:17:16,860 --> 00:17:20,980
I think I like you.

234
00:17:45,730 --> 00:17:47,430
Or love?

235
00:18:08,845 --> 00:18:10,840
They were beautiful.

236
00:18:10,840 --> 00:18:12,640
Yeah.

237
00:18:12,640 --> 00:18:17,575
Will you come to the drinking party after this?

238
00:18:17,575 --> 00:18:19,760
I think I'll pass after all...

239
00:18:19,760 --> 00:18:21,340
My feet are tired, too.

240
00:18:21,340 --> 00:18:23,525
Huh? Are you okay?

241
00:18:23,525 --> 00:18:25,595
Yeah, I'm fine.

242
00:18:27,650 --> 00:18:30,840
We can go as slow as you'd like.

243
00:18:31,875 --> 00:18:35,050
Okay. Thank you.

244
00:18:40,985 --> 00:18:42,820
Are you okay?

245
00:18:42,820 --> 00:18:44,220
Yeah.

246
00:18:45,490 --> 00:18:48,900
You'll be at the party later, right?

247
00:18:48,900 --> 00:18:50,820
Um... Sure.

248
00:18:50,820 --> 00:18:52,499
Huh? You're coming, right?

249
00:18:52,499 --> 00:18:55,124
- Yeah.
- That's great.

250
00:18:58,125 --> 00:19:00,390
The fireworks were really beautiful.

251
00:19:00,390 --> 00:19:01,790
Yeah.

252
00:19:04,425 --> 00:19:06,850
Have a nice rest.

253
00:19:06,850 --> 00:19:08,970
Yeah, thank you.

254
00:19:08,970 --> 00:19:11,753
How are your feet?

255
00:19:11,753 --> 00:19:16,095
Good. I'll be fine soon. Thank you.

256
00:19:16,095 --> 00:19:18,890
Well then, take care.

257
00:19:19,645 --> 00:19:23,490
- Good night.
- Good night.

258
00:19:34,780 --> 00:19:38,430
Kusaka-san is so kind.

259
00:19:38,430 --> 00:19:40,210
But...

260
00:19:42,660 --> 00:19:46,080
that sensation still hasn't faded.

261
00:19:56,360 --> 00:19:58,400
Coming!

262
00:20:05,060 --> 00:20:06,570
Huh?

263
00:20:08,150 --> 00:20:10,520
Let me in.

264
00:20:14,495 --> 00:20:19,021
This is ridiculous! I can't believe him.

265
00:20:19,021 --> 00:20:21,095
Miporin?

266
00:20:21,095 --> 00:20:23,160
Miporin!

267
00:20:23,160 --> 00:20:24,675
- Miporin!
- You're too loud!

268
00:20:24,675 --> 00:20:27,235
Just shut up and get in.

269
00:20:32,800 --> 00:20:36,550
Wow, it's huge.

270
00:20:36,550 --> 00:20:39,170
- Yay!
- Jeez!

271
00:20:39,170 --> 00:20:41,970
Hey, don't just barge in here!

272
00:20:41,970 --> 00:20:43,925
What if Yuri-chan and the others come back?

273
00:20:43,925 --> 00:20:46,245
Hurry and get out!

274
00:20:47,980 --> 00:20:49,680
Hey.

275
00:20:52,730 --> 00:20:56,410
Why do you think I called for you?

276
00:21:19,600 --> 00:21:26,360
♫ We walked through the city at daybreak,
soaked by the rain ♫

277
00:21:26,360 --> 00:21:30,690
♫ You and me in the rain ♫

278
00:21:30,690 --> 00:21:33,980
Wait. Not here...

279
00:21:35,280 --> 00:21:40,720
♫ I want to be someone others trust ♫

280
00:21:40,720 --> 00:21:44,370
♫ I kept looking at you ♫

281
00:21:45,380 --> 00:21:52,410
♫ Hold me close, stay by my side ♫

282
00:21:52,410 --> 00:21:55,950
♫ Don't let go... ♫

283
00:21:55,950 --> 00:21:59,170
♫ Of my hand ♫

284
00:21:59,170 --> 00:22:06,210
♫ If the rain could dissolve
the two of us like this ♫

285
00:22:06,210 --> 00:22:09,620
♫ We wouldn't... ♫

286
00:22:09,620 --> 00:22:15,120
♫ Need to think about tomorrow ♫

287
00:22:23,110 --> 00:22:30,080
♫ Hold me close, stay by my side ♫

288
00:22:30,080 --> 00:22:33,630
♫ Don't let go... ♫

289
00:22:33,630 --> 00:22:35,070
[Room 16]

290
00:22:35,075 --> 00:22:36,360
There's beer for sure.

291
00:22:36,360 --> 00:22:38,758
And the manager got excited

292
00:22:38,758 --> 00:22:41,870
and brought some
famous something shochu*,

293
00:22:41,870 --> 00:22:43,080
and nihonshu* too.
(*Japanese alcoholic beverages)

294
00:22:43,080 --> 00:22:45,566
- "Something" shochu?
- I don't know.

295
00:22:45,566 --> 00:22:48,011
- Let's fix our makeup.
- Okay.

296
00:22:49,690 --> 00:22:52,480
Mihono-san.

297
00:22:53,273 --> 00:22:55,700
Oh. She's already asleep.

298
00:22:55,700 --> 00:22:56,900
Seriously?

299
00:22:56,900 --> 00:22:58,860
She must have been tired.

300
00:22:58,860 --> 00:23:02,250
She's from a different team,
so she must be drained mentally.

301
00:23:02,250 --> 00:23:04,160
Maybe I shouldn't have forced her to come.

302
00:23:04,160 --> 00:23:06,285
It's fine. We'll just let her sleep.

303
00:23:06,285 --> 00:23:08,075
Yeah, you're right.

304
00:23:13,730 --> 00:23:17,310
That's why I said no!

305
00:23:23,820 --> 00:23:26,839
The heat from that day still hasn't cooled down.
[Preview]

306
00:23:26,839 --> 00:23:30,580
I wonder why we aren't dating.

307
00:23:30,580 --> 00:23:34,715
- It's love, right?
- I'm telling you, I don't know.

308
00:23:34,715 --> 00:23:35,843
Isn't this awesome?
[Dinner with Ureshino-san!]

309
00:23:35,843 --> 00:23:39,906
I bet girls like her are his real type.

310
00:23:39,906 --> 00:23:43,866
I want to learn more about you, Onuma-san.

311
00:23:44,665 --> 00:23:48,661
I was seen going into your room.

312
00:23:48,661 --> 00:23:53,333
I'm losing my ability to think straight.
[This drama is fiction.]
